<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-erasedlost" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Erased and Lost</head>
    <p><!--gloss--></p>
    <p><specList>
            <specDesc key="del"/>
            <specDesc key="gap"/>
        </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p>

    <p>Characters erased in antiquity and completely lost should be tagged using the <gi>del</gi>
        element, assigning to the <att>rend</att> attribute the value "erasure". A <gi>gap</gi>
        element should be placed inside the <gi>del</gi> and given <att>reason</att>,
            <att>quantity</att> and <att>unit</att> attributes.</p>

    <cit>
        <quote>[[[...]]] or [[[<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="superscript">c.7</hi></hi>]]] or [[[---]]]</quote>
        <bibl corresp="#panciera">
            <biblScope>V.3</biblScope>
        </bibl>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <del rend="erasure"><gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/></del>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="http://irt.kcl.ac.uk/irt2009/IRT445.html">
        <del rend="erasure"><gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/></del>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="http://www.papyri.info/ddbdp/bgu;7;1621"> 
        <del rend="erasure"><gap reason="illegible" quantity="3" unit="character"/></del>
    </egXML>
    
    <div xml:id="trans-erasedlost-responsibility">

        <head>Responsibility for this section</head>
        <listBibl>
            <bibl><respStmt>
                    <resp>author</resp>
                    <name>Beatrice Lietz</name>
                </respStmt></bibl>
            <bibl><respStmt>
                    <resp>author</resp>
                    <name>Charlotte Tupman</name>
                </respStmt></bibl>
        </listBibl>
    </div>
</div>
